            <div id="document"><p><span style="color: rgb(126, 140, 141);">Name:</span></p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;">Assignment 15</h1>
<h4 style="text-align: center;">Due: Tuesday, April 7</h4>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Here it is, future mathematicians!&nbsp; More proofs!&nbsp; These are like eating peanuts... there are a lot, but they are mostly bite-sized!&nbsp; In these problems upper case variables are sets.&nbsp; Be sure to specify your reasons for all of these.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span> - easy<br><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span> - moderate<br><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span> - more challenging</span></p>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(45, 194, 107); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">&nbsp; Problem 1.<strong> </strong></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;theorem&quot;" data-shell_title="Theorem:">
<p><strong>Theorem 9.5 (double negative).</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;(A')'=A&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.801892em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.81em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.39em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">&prime;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.93em;"><span style="top: -3.53em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.39em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">&prime;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;proof&quot;" data-shell_title="Proof:">
<p><strong>Proof:</strong>&nbsp;<br><br></p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\square&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__ams">□</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(45, 194, 107); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">&nbsp; Problem 2.<strong> </strong></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;theorem&quot;" data-shell_title="Theorem:">
<p><strong>Theorem 9.7 (a set of sets). </strong>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;{1,2} in { A : {1} subset A }&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8388800000000001em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__cmr">1,</span><span class="ML__cmr">2</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">&isin;</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.25em; height: 1em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">:</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.64444em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__cmr">1</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">&sube;</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span></span></span></span></span><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;proof&quot;" data-shell_title="Proof:">
<p><strong>Proof:</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\square&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__ams">□</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(45, 194, 107); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">&nbsp; Problem 3.<strong> </strong></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span> Tip: don't forget to say 'by cases' and 'by substitution' when you use those rules.</p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;theorem&quot;" data-shell_title="Theorem:">
<p><strong>Theorem 9.8 (Cartesian calculation).&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;{2} cross {3,5} = {[2,3],[2,5]}&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.64444em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__cmr">2</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">&times;</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8388800000000001em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__cmr">3,</span><span class="ML__cmr">5</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.25em; height: 1em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8388800000000001em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">⟨</span><span class="ML__cmr">2,</span><span class="ML__cmr">3</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">⟩</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8388800000000001em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">⟨</span><span class="ML__cmr">2,</span><span class="ML__cmr">5</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">⟩</span></span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;proof&quot;" data-shell_title="Proof:">
<p><strong>Proof:</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\square&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__ams">□</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(45, 194, 107); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">&nbsp; Problem 4.<strong> </strong></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;theorem&quot;" data-shell_title="Theorem:">
<p><strong>Theorem 9.22 (relative complement is not associative).</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If x in A cap (B cap C)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">&isin;</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">&cap;</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.68333em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span><span class="ML__cmr">&cap;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">C</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;A setminus (B setminus C) neq (A setminus B) setminus C&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">∖</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.25em; height: 1em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span><span class="ML__cmr">∖</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">C</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span><span class="ML__rlap"><span class="ML__inner"><span class="ML__cmr"></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.25em; height: 1em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">∖</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">∖</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">C</span></span></span></span></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;proof&quot;" data-shell_title="Proof:">
<p><strong>Proof:</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\square&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__ams">□</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(45, 194, 107); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">&nbsp; Problem 5.<strong> </strong></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;theorem&quot;" data-shell_title="Theorem:">
<p><strong>Theorem 9.30 (even more De Morgan).</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom atom-is-selected" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;(Union i in I of A_(i))'=Intersect j in I of A_(j)'&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -1.321706em; height: 2.3717110000000003em;"><span class="ML__open ML__delim-size4">(</span><span class="ML__op-group"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 1.06em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -1.85em;"><span style="height: 0.51em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__mathit">i</span><span class="ML__cmr">&isin;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">I</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.05em;"><span style="height: 1.61em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__op-symbol ML__large-op">⋃</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.32em;"><span style="top: -2.85em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.47em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__mathit">i</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__close ML__delim-size4">)</span></span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 1.87em;"><span style="top: -4.47em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.39em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">&prime;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__op-group"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 1.06em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -1.85em;"><span style="height: 0.62em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">j</span><span class="ML__cmr">&isin;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">I</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.05em;"><span style="height: 1.61em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__op-symbol ML__large-op">⋂</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.32em;"><span style="top: -2.85em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.6em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">j</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.81em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.39em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">&prime;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;proof&quot;" data-shell_title="Proof:">
<p><strong>Proof:</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\square&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__ams">□</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(45, 194, 107); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">&nbsp; Problem 6.<strong> </strong></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;theorem&quot;" data-shell_title="Theorem:">
